-- Emirates Steel Starts $650 Million Abu Dhabi Heavy Section Plant
-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 2012-01-03T06:16:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/emirates-steel-starts-650-million-abu-dhabi-heavy-section-plant.html
Emirates Steel Industries PJSC, the
state-owned company that operates the largest steel plant in the
United Arab Emirates, said its $650 million Heavy Section Mill
started operations.  Abu Dhabi-based Emirates Steel is now the only producer of
jumbo and heavy sections in the  Middle East  and  Africa , Chairman
Suhail al-Ameri said in an e-mailed statement yesterday.  The company added that it now has an annual direct-reduced
iron capacity for 3.2 million metric tons and steel-making
capacity for 2.8 million tons. Total output will reach 6.5
million tons a year in four years, Emirates Steel said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ayesha Daya in Dubai at 
